        {
          "activity_type": "patch_reviewed",
          "subject": "Re: [PATCH v2] btrfs: use IOMAP_DIO_BOUNCE flag instead of falling back to buffered IO",
          "message_id": "20260526175955.GA1359754@zen.localdomain",
          "url": "https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260526175955.GA1359754@zen.localdomain/",
          "date": "2026-05-26T18:00:16Z",
          "in_reply_to": null,
          "ack_type": null,
          "is_ongoing": false,
          "submitted_date": null,
          "patch_version": 1,
          "series_patch_count": null,
          "version_history": [],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch updates Btrfs to use the IOMAP_DIO_BOUNCE flag instead of falling back to buffered IO, which is expected to improve performance. The previous fallback to buffered IO was likely introducing unnecessary overhead due to its synchronous nature and additional work required for page cache management. By using the bounce flag, the patch aims to reduce this overhead and make Btrfs operations more efficient.",
          "analysis_source": "llm-per-reviewer",
          "review_comments": [
            {
              "author": "Qu Wenruo",
              "summary": "Reviewer noted that the new bounce behavior exposes problems related to page faults during write, specifically a bug in nodatasum mount option generic/362, which can fail due to failed page fault-in and handling of later buffered fallback.",
              "sentiment": "NEEDS_WORK",
              "sentiment_signals": [
                "requested changes"
              ],
              "has_inline_review": false,
              "tags_given": [
                "Reviewed-by"
              ],
              "raw_body": "I guess it's mostly due to the page cache synchronization.\n\n\nBut please do not be too excited for now, this new bounce behavior \nexposes several problems, mostly related to the page fault during write.\n\nIt exposed a bug that even without this patch, for nodatasum mount \noption that generic/362 (*) can still fail due to failed page fault-in \nand handling of later buffered fallback.\n\n*: Needs this patch to reliably trigger the failure, or it will only \nfail with newly formatted TEST_DEV: \nhttps://lore.kernel.org/linux-btrfs/20260526070055.60193-1-wqu@suse.com/T/#u\n\nThanks,\nQu",
              "reply_to": "Boris Burkov",
              "message_date": "2026-05-27",
              "message_id": "7f0ab384-c077-4ec2-8f74-049e3963fb5a@suse.com",
              "analysis_source": "llm",
              "email": "wqu@suse.com"
            }
          ],
          "list_id": "linux-btrfs@vger.kernel.org"
        }
      ],
